      "id": "00dafe05_31db1f87",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/dmaap-dr-node/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "Same question re other template patch. If pod goes down/rescheduled, will init container re-run to fetch aaf artifacts? This was main reason for persisting them on the nfs.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4405,
        "name": "Fiachra Corcoran",
        "display_name": "Fiachra Corcoran (EST)",
        "email": "fiachra.corcoran@est.tech",
        "username": "efiacor"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-01 09:43:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "6deb5e10_17e12fbd",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/dmaap-dr-node/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "if pod goes down --> K8S will relaunch it _but_ with the configmaps of the previous one so it'll retrieve the right configuration.\na pod is not actually rescheduled in K8S terms (https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod/#what-is-a-pod) but recreated and then init part will  work too",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2319,
        "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
        "username": "sdesbure"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-01 09:59:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "00dafe05_31db1f87",
      "unresolved": true
    },
