      "message": "I've made a local helper.\nI'll see later if I move to a global one.\nBy the way, I'm a bit unsure to understand \"common.secret.buildCache\"\nI line _secret.tpl#L186, you won't build the cache if `$global.Values._secretsCache` is not present.\n\nI do understand that for \"one chart\" deploy (mariadb for example) it'll work.\n\nBut for DMaaP for example, let's say first chart being created by helm is dmaap-bc.\nWhen we move to dmaap-dr-node, `$global.Values._secretsCache` is set and then we don't add its own values no?\nOr Am I wrong somewhere (as it works, I assume I'm wrong ;) )?",
