    {
      "id": "5f814238_ee0a3663",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/dmaap-dr-node/resources/config/node.properties",
      "patchset_number": 11,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "> I've made a local helper.\n> I'll see later if I move to a global one.\n> By the way, I'm a bit unsure to understand \"common.secret.buildCache\"\n> I line _secret.tpl#L186, you won't build the cache if `$global.Values._secretsCache` is not present.\n\nactually it's the other way around. I build the cache if `$global.Values._secretsCache`is not present.\n\n> \n> I do understand that for \"one chart\" deploy (mariadb for example) it'll work.\n> \n> But for DMaaP for example, let's say first chart being created by helm is dmaap-bc.\n> When we move to dmaap-dr-node, `$global.Values._secretsCache` is set and then we don't add its own values no?\n> Or Am I wrong somewhere (as it works, I assume I'm wrong ;) )?\n\nYou are so wrong as the guy who designed Public transport fares in Paris:D\n\nEvery chart has its own set of values. Whenever you go from one chart to another one .Values are cleaned up so you would rebuild the cache once again. There are only 2 things copied from parent chart to children:\n1) global section ($global.Values.global in this case)\n2) Overrides (For example everything in dmaap-dr-node node in dmaap values)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-15 09:44:28.000000000",
